{
  "topicId": "m5-t1",
  "title": "Asking about the location of things",
  "dialect": "darija",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Introducing 'Where?' - فين؟",
          "arabic": "فين؟"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'Where?' in Moroccan Darija, we use the word 'فين'. It's a fundamental question word for inquiring about location.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فين؟",
            "english": "Where?",
            "transliteration": "Fīn?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين هو؟",
            "english": "Where is he/it? (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "Fīn hūwa?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين هي؟",
            "english": "Where is she/it? (fem.)",
            "transliteration": "Fīn hiyya?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Where is the...?' - Basic Structure",
          "arabic": "فين الـ...؟"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'Where is the [object]?', you simply place the object after 'فين'. The definite article 'الـ' (el-) is usually attached to the noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فين الكتاب؟",
            "english": "Where is the book?",
            "transliteration": "Fīn el-ktāb?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين السيارة؟",
            "english": "Where is the car?",
            "transliteration": "Fīn es-siyāra?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين الحمام؟",
            "english": "Where is the bathroom?",
            "transliteration": "Fīn el-ḥammām?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "The Verb 'To Be' (for location): كاين/كاينا",
          "arabic": "كاين/كاينا"
        },
        "text": "In Darija, when asking or stating location, we often use 'كاين' (kāyn) for masculine singular and 'كاينا' (kāyna) for feminine singular, meaning 'is present' or 'is located'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فين كاين الستيلو؟",
            "english": "Where is the pen? (pen is masculine)",
            "transliteration": "Fīn kāyn es-stīlo?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "فين كاينا المحفظة؟",
            "english": "Where is the bag? (bag is feminine)",
            "transliteration": "Fīn kāyna el-maḥfaḍa?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الكتاب كاين هنا.",
            "english": "The book is here. (masc.)",
            "transliteration": "El-ktāb kāyn hna."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "فين كاين الدار؟",
        "english": "Where is the house?",
        "transliteration": "Fīn kāyn ed-dār?"
      },
      "context": "Asking about the location of a house (ed-dār is masculine in this context in Darija)."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "فين كاينا الساعة؟",
