    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition 'In Front Of' - قدام",
          "arabic": "قدام"
        },
        "text": "The preposition 'قدام' (giddām) means 'in front of'. It indicates that something is directly ahead or facing another object.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "السيارة قدام الدار.",
            "english": "The car is in front of the house.",
            "transliteration": "Es-siyāra giddām ed-dār."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أنا جالس قدام الباب.",
            "english": "I am sitting in front of the door.",
            "transliteration": "Ana jāles giddām el-bāb."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition 'Behind' - مورَا",
          "arabic": "مورَا"
        },
        "text": "The preposition 'مورَا' (mōrā) means 'behind'. It indicates that something is at the back of another object. This is the opposite of 'قدام'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الشجرة مورَا الحيط.",
            "english": "The tree is behind the wall.",
            "transliteration": "Esh-shajra mōrā el-ḥīṭ."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الكلب مورَا الباب.",
            "english": "The dog is behind the door.",
            "transliteration": "El-kelb mōrā el-bāb."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition 'Next To / Beside' - حدَا",
          "arabic": "حدَا"
