    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition 'Between' - بين",
          "arabic": "بين"
        },
        "text": "The preposition 'بين' (bīn) means 'between'. It is used to describe an object situated in the middle of two other objects or places.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "الطبلة بين الكراسا.",
            "english": "The table is between the chairs.",
            "transliteration": "Eṭ-ṭbla bīn el-krāsa."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الخزانة بين الحيوط.",
            "english": "The closet is between the walls.",
            "transliteration": "El-khzāna bīn el-ḥyūṭ."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition 'On the Right' - على اليمين",
          "arabic": "على اليمين"
        },
        "text": "To say 'on the right', we use 'على اليمين' (ʿalā l-ymīn). This indicates a direction or position to the right side.",
